HEADWORD: Overtax
<hw>O`ver*tax"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To tax or to
task too heavily; <as>as, a job that <ex>overtaxed</ex> his physical
energies</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

